SENATE RESOLUTION 20
By Lamar
A RESOLUTION to honor Dr. LaDonna Boyd in celebration of
Women's Day on the Hill.
WHEREAS, Women's Day on the Hill is a time to honor the achievements of those
Tennessee women who have paved the way for every person to have the opportunity to pursue
the American dream; and
WHEREAS, the Volunteer State is proud to be the home of the awe-inspiring Dr.
LaDonna Boyd, who serves as the fifth-generation President/CEO of the R.H. Boyd Family of
Companies in Nashville, in which position she has proven herself a powerhouse of innovation
and creativity, transforming the business landscape while championing social causes close to
her heart; and
WHEREAS, an advocate for economic empowerment, she is dedicated to creating
opportunities for underserved communities, elevating educational access for all, and driving
forward wellness initiatives; and
WHEREAS, she has further served her fellow citizens by devoting her time and talents
to various organizations, including Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc.; the National Museum of
African American Music; the National Museum of African American History and Culture, of
which she is a founding member; the Nashville Ballet; the Metro Davidson County Historic
Zoning Commission; the Evangelical Christian Publishers Association; the Economic and
Finance Advisory Board for the College of Business at Tennessee State University; and the
Holding Company for Citizens Savings Bank and Trust, which she currently serves as chair; and
WHEREAS, in saluting Dr. Boyd on this special occasion, let us remember that when
women succeed, America succeeds, as does Tennessee; now, therefore,
